article_title: Q&A: Get to know Sandra Martell, Winnebago County’s new public health administrator
article_text:
Rockford Register Star By Susan Vela Rockford Register Star

Posted Sep. 29, 2014 at 10:33 AM

Updated Sep 29, 2014 at 4:54 PM

article_metadata.description: ROCKFORD — Sandra Martell is new at the helm of the Winnebago County Health Department. She replaced Mike Bacon, who retired from the agency after 17 years as the public health administrator.Martell’s 25 years of public health experience include a recent stint as interim chief operating officer for the Cook County Department of Public Health. She has a doctorate in nursing practice and a master’s degree in public health nursing/family nurse practitioner.In her new position,
